       These functions place characters and renditions  from  the
       current  or  specified window into the array pointed to by
       chstr, starting at the current or specified  position  and
       ending at the end of the line.

       The  and  functions store at most n elements from the cur-
       rent or specified window into  the  array  pointed  to  by
       chstr.

